   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="uoedh_hl_h.3184_1.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <address rend="letterhead">
                  <addrLine>The Little Orchard</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>Shoreham</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>Kent</addrLine>
               </address>
               <dateline>
                  <date when="1915-05-28">May 28.|15</date>
               </dateline>
               <salute>My dear friend:</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>My sincerest thanks for your delightfully worded testimony to the value of my good
               old faithful friend. You will see, by enclosure, how truly grateful she is –.</p>

            <p>It <choice><abbr>w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>.</abbr>
                  <expan>would</expan></choice> have been very nice to have had some talks with you
               in this quiet sunny orchard, – &amp; you know I <choice><abbr>w<hi rend="superscript"
                        >d</hi></abbr>
                  <expan>would</expan></choice>. have done my <hi rend="underline">best</hi> to make
               you comfortable –, &amp; not to let you be too tired here –. <pb n="2"
                  facs="uoedh_hl_h.3184_2.jpg"/> But I can <hi rend="underline">quite</hi>
               understand <choice><abbr>y<hi rend="superscript"
                     >r</hi>.</abbr><expan>your</expan><expan>your</expan></choice>
               <hi rend="underline">distaste</hi> for journeys –.</p>

            <p>I hope that dear <persName ref="#ps:FlorenceHardy">Florence</persName>'s little
               operation will be a <hi rend="underline">complete</hi> success. I am so sorry not to
               be in <placeName ref="#pl:London">London</placeName> to see her in the Home –</p>

            <p>The Coalition <choice><abbr>Govt.</abbr>
                  <expan>Government</expan></choice> is certainly very interesting, though I think
               it ought to have included <persName ref="#ps:LordMilner">Lord Milner</persName>, who
               has done <pb n="3" facs="uoedh_hl_h.3184_3.jpg"/> his best for years to wake up the
               country – &amp; who is so single-minded &amp; honest a statesman. – I should like
               very much, to hear <persName ref="#ps:LordMorley"><choice><abbr>L<hi
                           rend="superscript">d</hi>.</abbr>
                     <expan>Lord</expan></choice>
                  <hi rend="underline">Morley</hi></persName> explain his point of view. Probably
               his health has something to do with his attitude – but it is more likely the
               principle of <hi rend="underline">non-interference</hi> carried to excess – don't you
               think? –</p>

            <p>I thought the lines in today's "<orgName ref="#psTheTimes">Times</orgName>" by poor
                  <persName ref="#ps:JulianGrenfell"><choice><abbr>Capt</abbr>
                     <expan>Captain</expan></choice> Grenfell</persName> rather striking to <pb
                  n="4" facs="uoedh_hl_h.3184_4.jpg"/> have been written by a young soldier. And I
               like his tenderness for birds &amp; horses – in the midst of all the surrounding
               horror –</p>

            <p>I hope you are feeling well – &amp; that the vein in <choice><abbr>yr.</abbr>
                  <expan>your</expan></choice> leg does not trouble you, or prevent you from
               enjoying this lovely May.</p>

            <closer>
               <salute><choice><abbr>Ev</abbr>
                     <expan>Ever</expan></choice>
                  <choice><abbr>yr</abbr>
                     <expan>your</expan></choice>
                  <choice><abbr>affec.</abbr>
                     <expan>affectionate</expan></choice> friend</salute>
               <signed>Flo H</signed>
            </closer>

         </div>
      </body>
